{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Parliament to allow the electorate to have a yes or no referendum on referendums",
        "additional_details": "Some requests for referendums on the petition website: \r\nHold a referendum on the final Brexit deal \r\nStop possible second referendum on E.U. membership \r\nHold a referendum for the legalisation of cannabis \r\nIn 2019 hold a referendum to reinstate capital punishment \r\nAll UK citizens have the right to vote on referendums affecting the UK's future. \r\nHold a referendum on Proportional Representation for parliamentary elections",
        "background": "We the public are being constantly told we must have another referendum for different issues. Do we as a country want to have them in our constitution, do we have a vote on the same issue every 2 or 5 years like some want on the EU issue.\r\n \r\n",
